OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1780578664
OL,3,CTube strike causes travel disruption
OL,4,Cacross London
OL,6,FThe first of two 24-hour strikes by
OL,7,FLondon Underground drivers has caused
OL,8,Fhuge disruption to Tube services
OL,9,Facross the capital, with further
OL,10,Findustrial action planned.
OL,12,FMembers of the Rail, Maritime and
OL,13,FTransport union (RMT) walked out on
OL,14,FTuesday and will strike again on
OL,15,FThursday after last-ditch talks failed
OL,16,Fto resolve a dispute over the working
OL,17,Fweek.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1780578664
OL,3,CTube strike causes travel disruption
OL,4,Cacross London
OL,6,FThe union said the action was strongly
OL,7,Fsupported, but Transport for London
OL,8,F(TfL) said 60% of drivers turned up
OL,9,Ffor work.The RMT said it expects fresh
OL,10,Ftalks to be held next week.
OL,12,FA TfL spokesperson said: "We are sorry
OL,13,Fthat today has been difficult for
OL,14,Fcustomers and for London's business,
OL,15,Fbut are pleased that we have been able
OL,16,Fto offer service on almost every Tube
OL,17,Fline today despite the strike action
OL,18,Ftaken by the RMT, including the
OL,19,FJubilee Line operating a normal
OL,20,Fservice."
OL,26,@tD@ZOU|D@IOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1780578664
OL,3,CTube strike causes travel disruption
OL,4,Cacross London
OL,6,FOnly a handful of drivers had stayed
OL,7,Faway from work on the Jubilee Line,
OL,8,Fand overall around 60% of drivers came
OL,9,Fto work, which is more than in April's
OL,10,Fstrike action.
OL,12,F"We continue to urge the RMT to work
OL,13,Fwith us to resolve their questions on
OL,14,Fthe proposed four-day week and to
OL,15,Fsuspend any future action while that
OL,16,Fwork is completed."
OL,18,FAn RMT spokesperson said: "Our strike
OL,19,Fhas been strongly supported by RMT
OL,20,Fmembers with well attended picket
OL,21,Flines at Tube stations and depots.
OL,26,@tD@AOUxD@SO]zD@[OU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1780578664
OL,3,CTube strike causes travel disruption
OL,4,Cacross London
OL,6,F"We are available at any time for
OL,7,Ftalks to try to find a negotiated
OL,8,Fsettlement and expect to meet the
OL,9,Femployer next week."
OL,11,FTfL said its data up to 10am showed
OL,12,Faround 86% of Oyster and contactless
OL,13,Fcard taps had been recorded across the
OL,14,Fcapital on Tuesday compared to the
OL,15,Fequivalent day last year, meaning the
OL,16,Fvast majority of Londoners still
OL,17,Ftravelled with TfL getting to work,
OL,18,Fschool and more "despite the
OL,19,Fdisruptive action taken by the RMT".
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@TO]zD@QOU{D@cO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1780578664
OL,3,CTube strike causes travel disruption
OL,4,Cacross London
OL,6,FThere was some level of service on
OL,7,Fevery Tube line, other than the
OL,8,Fclosures planned for the strikes on
OL,9,Fthe Circle and Waterloo and City
OL,10,Flines, said TfL.
OL,12,FThe two sides met for five hours on
OL,13,FMonday, with the assistance of the
OL,14,Fconciliation service Acas, but the
OL,15,Ftalks ended without any resolution.
OL,17,FThe union is opposed to a new four-day
OL,18,Fweek because of the impact on the
OL,19,Flength of shifts and other issues.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
